article.description: Charles Cooke scored 21 points and Dayton beat Duquesne 66-58 on Saturday in an Atlantic 10 opener.
article.headline: Dayton beats Duquesne 66-58 in A-10 opener
article.linkText: Dayton beats Duquesne 66-58 in A-10 opener
article.story: PITTSBURGH -- Charles Cooke scored 21 points and Dayton beat Duquesne 66-58 on Saturday in an Atlantic 10 opener. Dayton (11-2) survived a poor shooting day to top the Dukes. Neither team shot over 37 percent from the floor, and they combined to go 5 of 37 from beyond the arc. Derrick Colter scored 14 points -- despite going 2 of 12 from the floor -- and Darius Lewis added 12 for Duquesne (10-4), which outrebounded the Flyers 44-37 -- but turned it over 18 times. Lewis hit a jumper and Colter made a pair at the line to draw the Dukes within four with 38 seconds left. They were forced to foul, though, and Dayton's Kyle Davis made 3 of 4 free throws and Cooke made 1 of 2 to ice it. Darrell Davis' 3-pointer with 25 seconds left in the first half gave Dayton a 25-20 lead at the break.
